column64: I am 65 years old and recently had cataract surgery done by Dr. Weisenthal.   I was able to get an appointment within weeks vs. months from another doctor. He had surgery completed for both eyes (monofocal lens for near sighted correction) within 2 weeks. Amazing how quick the surgery was (10 minutes), home within 3 hours. Could see the change right away. White balance was "colder", more true white, compared to the natural len's warmer white balance. Vision detail improvement was incredible, like going from VHS to 4K video. I could see details I don't ever remember seeing - i.e, blades of grass, hair strands on my dog. Night driving was no longer a problem. Only negative after affect are some "floaters" that should eventually go away. I only briefly saw Dr. Weisenthal but he was thorough, quick and professional. Staff was very accomodating. He runs a pretty smooth operation. I would suggest reading up on cataracts to bring questions for the appointments.

column64: Dr. Pill is hands-down an incredible doctor and surgeon.  After going through multiple doctors and specialists for YEARS, Dr. Pill was the first and only person to not only diagnose me, but create a successful plan for pregnancy.  He is accommodating, professional, and just has this innate ability to make you feel calm and well taken care of.  Sure, sometimes there can be a wait, but for me, incredible doctors are WORTH travel and/or wait times.  You can tell a lot about any leader by their team, and his colleagues - both in his office, and at Good Sam - seem to genuinely admire him.  After the birth of my son, I almost could not mention his name without becoming emotional over how well he had taken care of me and my family before, during, and after pregnancy.  Saying I highly recommend Dr. Pill is an understatement, I truly think he is amazing and exemplary of what every doctor should be!
